The euro weakened against its U.S.
and Japanese counterparts on concern  Europe ’s sovereign
borrowers and banks will struggle to raise funds.  The common currency slid 0.2 percent to $1.2921 and 99.13
yen at 10:29 a.m. in  Tokyo  from yesterday’s close in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
